author: Paramount Plus
description:
Written, directed and executive produced by Tyler Perry, "Sistas" follows a group of single black women as they navigate the ups and downs of modern life, which includes careers, friendships, romances, and even social media. The comedy-drama series features Andi Barnes (KJ Smith), an ambitious divorce lawyer, Danni King (Mignon), a funny and fearless airport employee, Karen Mott (Ebony Obsidian), a street-smart hair salon owner, and Sabrina Hollins (Novi Brown), a smart and stylish bank teller.

"The Pilot" - Andi braves the highs and lows of her special day. Karen makes a difficult decision. Sabrina entertains the prospect of new love.

Stream Tyler Perry's Sistas on Paramount+.

This Black History Month, celebrate stories that inspire and break down barriers.
